<br>
What should I wield in the following situations:<br>
<br>
Raid Situations where I am the MA<br>
<br>
Solo situations with my cleric husband.<br>
<br>
When I'm just a damage dealer in group.<br>
<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance for any tips.<br>
<br>
Bloodbringer Fearfyre<br>
Tier'dal Warlordess of 60 Seasons<br>
Officer of the League of Shadows<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxenojones.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XENOJONES</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 159<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/4/02 11:52:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Three weapons - what do I use?</span><hr size=1> If you are MT then use the frosty unless you are fighting cold resistant mobs. Your job is not to do the most damage, but keep aggro. I would suggest to use the general's sword in the offhand while MT, but depending on how much of a fire bonus the flaming dirk has I would consider it. Also if you have tanked the mob for a long time and your defense disc is down then switch to the Flaming dirk in primary (unless it is a FR mob in which case again go with the General's sword) After you have been taunting and procing on  a mob for a couple minutes and nobody is trying to take aggro from you then you might as well switch to the higher damage weapon. Now with that all said I am not sure of the side stats on the flaming dirk, but the general's sword is going to add 40 or so HPs to you so that is another consideration for using it in your offhand while MT.<br>
<br>
<br>
Frosty procs 60 some points of cold and an AC debuff that will piss mobs off, but depending on a proc for aggro can get you in trouble when it doesn't proc. Make sure you keep your dex up high.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Rollen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 875<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/5/02 12:06:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Three weapons - what do I use?</span><hr size=1> Flaming Dirk:  11 20, 3 fire damage, 10 sta 10 str 15 dex 15 agi 15 cold save.  I found it didn't do as much damage as I'd hoped... a 14 20 should outdamage Ragebringer primary, but it didn't really come close.  Oh well.  I'd say use the flambe dirk when exp grinding against blues.<br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel<br>
Dawn Rising <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxenojones.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XENOJONES</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/5/02 12:10:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Three weapons - what do I use?</span><hr size=1> Always use the flaming dirk based on those stats over the general's sword. I would use Frosty then against non-cold resistant mobs in the off hand over the general's and in primary as MT until aggro is sealed. Bring out the generals over the Frosty if you need to lose aggro.<br>
<br>
<br>
Rollen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 879<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/5/02 11:55:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Three weapons - what do I use?</span><hr size=1> I dunno Rollen, against even cons and up that dirk is basically 11 20 all the time, so I'd think the general's sword is better there.  Or are those stats really that important for a warrior?<br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel<br>
Dawn Rising <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubloodandsin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bloodandsin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 171<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/5/02 12:03:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Three weapons - what do I use?</span><hr size=1> Jarkell -  I've actually heard the exact opposite on dirk.  Majority of time its 14/20.  Did research on Alakazam, Steel Warrior and Safe House and asking around, and consensus is on Velious mobs, its 14/20, all the time, and most other times it is unless you get fire resistent mobs.  Perhaps you should re-test it, but honestly, I hit for a ton, real fast, when I have the dirk.<br>
<br>
I'm doing more testing. BAsically I use the Dirk all the time.  Using the following combos<br>
<br>
ornate primary/dirk secondary<br>
<br>
dirk primary/frosty secondary<br>
<br>
I dont use ornate primary/frosty secondary anymore.  The above two seem better overall. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New Mod!</span><br>  Posts: 557<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/5/02 3:49:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Three weapons - what do I use?</span><hr size=1>    I use an LSOEE, and am finding that while it's clearly running at 21/29 against green &amp; teal mobs, and usually 21/29 against low blues, it's rarely running higher than 16/29 against high blues &amp; above.  In other words, against the mobs where it really counts the elemental damage isn't coming into play much.<br>
<br>
   Granted, Magic resist is usually easier for mobs to resist than the others, but I thought I'd mention that.<br>
<br>
- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubloodandsin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bloodandsin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 172<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/5/02 4:21:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Three weapons - what do I use?</span><hr size=1> Just got back from Velks with the dirk. WOW.  High crit record for 195. 60% in the 40-75 range, 10% under, 15% 75-105.  Not too bad for someone with 200 str.<br>
<br>
I'm in love withe weapon.  Its probably best in the hands of 60, and if you in the low 50s, not as effective due to resists.  I'm a damange/taunting machine with it (though not uber by any means, hehe).<br>
